This page is the Staff & Hospital Resources section. After looking at the big picture and the patient lists, this page focuses on the "behind-the-scenes" people and tools that keep the hospital running.

In simple words, here is what this page shows:

1. Doctor & Nurse Performance
This section is all about the medical team. It helps the hospital see:

Workload: Which doctors are handling the most patients?

Specialties: A breakdown of staff by their expertise (like Surgeons, Pediatricians, or Nurses).

Efficiency: How many patients a staff member sees in a day.

2. Room and Bed Management
This part uses visuals to show the "physical" side of the hospital:

Occupancy: Which wards are full and which have space.

Turnover: How quickly a bed becomes available after a patient leaves. This is crucial for making sure new emergency patients have a place to go.

3. Equipment & Inventory
Sometimes this page includes "stock" information. It tracks important supplies to make sure the hospital doesn't run out of:

Medicines or vaccines.

Medical tools or PPE (masks and gloves).

Life-saving equipment like ventilators.

4. Scheduling & Shifts
You might see a calendar or a timeline here. It shows:

Who is working the night shift versus the day shift.

If there are enough people scheduled for the upcoming weekend.
